T1  - Managers' voting rights and corporate control
AU  - Mikkelson, Wayne H.
AU  - Partch, M.Megan
JO  - Journal of Financial Economics
VL  - 25
IS  - 2
SP  - 263
EP  - 290
PY  - 1989
DA  - 1989/12/01/
SN  - 0304-405X
DO  - https://doi.org/10.1016/0304-405X(89)90084-6
UR  - https://www.sciencedirect.com/science/article/pii/0304405X89900846
AB  - We document managers' vote holdings in a large random sample of industrial firms, and test whether the degree of managerial control of shares affects how often a firm is the target of control events. The likelihood of successful acquisitions of firms is unrelated to managers' holdings. But this insignificant relation reflects two opposing effects. Lower managerial control is associated with a higher probability that a firm will receive a takeover offer, but a lower probability that a takeover attempt will lead to a change in control.
