T1  - The information content of equity-for-debt swaps: An investigation of analyst forecasts of firm cash flows
AU  - Israel, Ronen
AU  - Ofer, Aharon R.
AU  - Siegel, Daniel R.
JO  - Journal of Financial Economics
VL  - 25
IS  - 2
SP  - 349
EP  - 370
PY  - 1989
DA  - 1989/12/01/
SN  - 0304-405X
DO  - https://doi.org/10.1016/0304-405X(89)90087-1
UR  - https://www.sciencedirect.com/science/article/pii/0304405X89900871
AB  - We demonstrate that analysts revise their forecasts of net operating income downward following the announcement of an equity-for-debt swap. Their revisions are positively correlated with the size of the stock-price reaction to the swap announcement. This evidence supports the hypothesis that announcements of equity-for-debt swaps convey information about the expected level of cash flows of the firm. We also provide evidence that this information is about transitory changes in the expected cash flows.
ER  - 

